HEADWORD: Bladderwort
<hw>Blad"der*wort`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus (<gen>Utricularia</gen>) of aquatic or marshy plants, which
usually bear numerous vesicles in the divisions of the leaves. These
serve as traps for minute animals. See <er>Ascidium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bladderwrack</ent>⟦br⟧
